cs.GT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper proposes a new game-theoretic framework to study interdependent security and defense in multi-agent systems under deliberate external attacks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper deals with security and defense in the context of deliberate attacks, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper uses a version of the real-world Internet-derived Autonomous Systems (AS) graph to generate instances of interdependent defense games, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper uses a version of the real-world Internet-derived Autonomous Systems (AS) graph to generate instances of interdependent defense games, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a simple learning heuristic to compute (approximate) mixed-strategy Nash equilibria in interdependent defense games, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence.
